Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:50.327 --> 00:52.543
NYPD. Open up.

00:53.146 --> 00:55.948
I have an arrest warrant
for Jamie Ruiz.

01:02.533 --> 01:03.700
NYPD.

01:09.240 --> 01:11.341
Aah!

01:12.844 --> 01:16.379
Ho-haw! Ma-ma-ma-maw!

01:16.398 --> 01:18.015
Ho-haw!

01:18.049 --> 01:20.267
Ma-ma-ma-maw!

01:20.318 --> 01:22.686
Ha! Ha! Ha! Ha! Ha!
Ha! Ha!

01:22.720 --> 01:24.387
<i>And</i> relax.

01:24.406 --> 01:26.023
And relax.

01:26.057 --> 01:28.025
I had a dream.

01:28.059 --> 01:30.277
I was floating
on a Lily pad,

01:30.328 --> 01:32.229
and the Swedish bikini team

01:32.247 --> 01:34.731
was reciting positive reviews
of "Naked Heat."

01:34.783 --> 01:35.962
Oh. Well,
that must have been lovely.

01:36.062 --> 01:37.073
Yeah.

01:37.102 --> 01:39.069
Why are you
telling us this?

01:39.087 --> 01:40.465
Well, because of you,
my Swedish paradise

01:40.565 --> 01:42.104
turned into
a wailing cat shelter.

01:42.204 --> 01:43.655
We're doing voice exercises

01:43.755 --> 01:45.572
to strengthen
abdominal breathing.

01:45.659 --> 01:46.604
At 5:00 A.M.?

01:46.704 --> 01:50.707
Preparation is the foundation
of an inspired audition.

01:50.741 --> 01:52.075
Ha ha!

01:52.109 --> 01:53.676
Mm.

01:55.572 --> 01:58.113
I mentioned to gram last night
that I was thinking about

01:58.213 --> 01:59.565
trying out for "Grease"
at my school.

02:00.213 --> 02:02.197
Oh. The old
"gram goes overboard

02:02.232 --> 02:04.596
because acting is in your bones" routine.
Apparently.

02:04.634 --> 02:06.101
Yeah, yeah.

02:06.136 --> 02:08.103
Rookie move, telling her
about the audition.

02:08.138 --> 02:09.586
I wasn't sure I'd have time
with all my other clubs,

02:09.674 --> 02:11.231
but I thought
it might be fun.

02:11.597 --> 02:13.719
I didn't know she'd wake me up
when it was still dark outside.

02:13.765 --> 02:14.298
I see.

02:14.299 --> 02:17.517
An actor learns to make
sacrifices for his craft.

02:18.314 --> 02:20.798
Besides, we'll all have
plenty of time to sleep

02:20.816 --> 02:23.301
when we're dead.

02:26.405 --> 02:28.356
Oh, speaking of dead.

02:28.407 --> 02:29.908
Castle.

02:29.942 --> 02:33.278
Nah. No, no, don't be silly.
Of course I was up.

02:33.312 --> 02:35.030
Jeez.
What's the big hurry?

02:35.081 --> 02:37.248
Victim's not going anywhere,
right?

02:37.283 --> 02:38.750
This one's different.

02:38.784 --> 02:40.864
- Lanie.
- Heard we got an officer down.

02:41.134 --> 02:43.252
- Yep. That's the word.
- Who is it?

02:43.282 --> 02:45.900
Don't know, but a cab driver
called 9-1-1

02:45.985 --> 02:48.653
after he parked
and stopped for a smoke.

02:48.687 --> 02:50.705
Let's see.

02:53.292 --> 02:56.528
Single gunshot wound
to the chest.

02:56.562 --> 02:58.833
And our guy isn't wearing
his Kevlar.

02:58.933 --> 03:01.268
Mind if I step in there
for a sec?

03:07.199 --> 03:09.064
It's from the 116 in Queens.

03:09.164 --> 03:11.032
This is an old-style badge,
though.

03:11.066 --> 03:13.334
Maybe he's old-school, didn't
want to give up the badge

03:13.368 --> 03:14.440
he built his career on.

03:14.540 --> 03:15.996
Castle, he's mid-20s.

03:16.071 --> 03:19.239
You ever heard of a brilliant
doctor named Doogie Howser?

03:22.411 --> 03:25.547
It's fake.

03:27.450 --> 03:29.219
That's Tequila.

03:29.386 --> 03:31.525
That's cheap Tequila.

03:33.189 --> 03:34.935
And he needed a refill.

03:37.820 --> 03:39.433
So a squirt gun
and an old badge--

03:39.533 --> 03:41.501
clearly he's not a cop.

03:42.469 --> 03:45.090
Maybe he was impersonating one
to prey on vulnerable women.

03:45.190 --> 03:46.686
Armed with
a Tequila pistol?

03:46.923 --> 03:49.558
Actually, I think women
were preying on him.

03:50.632 --> 03:53.101
Tear away pants?

03:53.135 --> 03:55.803
He's a stripper.
I'm not finding any I.D.

03:57.573 --> 04:00.308
He does have a car.

04:04.513 --> 04:07.315
Of all the cases in the city,
and it's a big city,

04:07.333 --> 04:09.334
you catch a male stripper.

04:09.368 --> 04:11.319
Yeah. Well, luck of the draw,
I guess.

04:11.337 --> 04:13.487
Yeah. I'm--I'm just sayin'.

04:13.506 --> 04:15.557
I'm just sayin'.
Shotgun.

04:15.591 --> 04:17.454
Castle,
you're the only one here.

04:17.774 --> 04:19.160
Yes.

04:22.096 --> 04:24.098
Ew.

04:25.634 --> 04:27.880
This place reminds me
of my first dorm room.

04:35.554 --> 04:37.373
Victim's name
is Derek Brookner.

04:37.473 --> 04:39.140
He's 27.

04:41.979 --> 04:44.681
Hey. He wrote an address on
the back of this deposit slip.

04:44.715 --> 04:47.283
"423 West 59th. 4-B."

04:47.733 --> 04:49.246
That's right around
the corner.

04:49.398 --> 04:50.911
And his body
was found halfway between

04:51.011 --> 04:52.078
that location and this car.

04:52.178 --> 04:53.934
What do you want to bet
that's where he was coming from?

04:58.343 --> 05:01.913
NYPD. Open up!

05:05.762 --> 05:08.140
Still sleeping. Go away.

05:10.545 --> 05:12.045
Oh.

05:12.064 --> 05:14.682
Excuse me. Sorry.

05:14.716 --> 05:17.384
Wow.

05:17.402 --> 05:19.019
Oh.

05:19.054 --> 05:21.439
Wow.

05:21.490 --> 05:23.844
Wow. Wow.

05:24.054 --> 05:26.639
That--they--whoa.

05:26.674 --> 05:28.541
They make cakes in that shape?
That--

05:28.559 --> 05:30.176
ooh!

05:30.210 --> 05:32.812
Another stripper?

05:32.846 --> 05:35.265
Whoo! Take it off!
Whoo!

05:35.316 --> 05:37.817
Take it off. Take it--
mm-hmm.

05:37.851 --> 05:39.741
Ladies, I am not a stripper,
though I can understand

05:39.841 --> 05:41.054
how you'd make that mistake.

05:41.340 --> 05:44.055
NYPD--the ones
with the real guns.

05:44.155 --> 05:46.961
We're here to investigate
the murder of Derek Brookner.

05:47.092 --> 05:48.329
We believe
he was your entertainment

05:48.429 --> 05:49.680
for last night's soiree.

05:49.780 --> 05:51.670
Oh, my God.
Officer McNaughty?

05:51.770 --> 05:52.701
I need to know

05:52.714 --> 05:54.781
the exact time that he arrived
and left yesterday.

05:55.374 --> 05:58.175
- It was dark.
- And his dance was long.

05:58.210 --> 06:00.010
That's not all
that was long.

06:03.795 --> 06:06.463
All right, let's pack it up.
I think a trip

06:06.497 --> 06:08.702
down to the station
will jog everyone's memories.

06:08.802 --> 06:10.803
Could we stop
and get brunch on the way?

06:15.175 --> 06:17.727
Ohh.

06:17.778 --> 06:19.412
Ms. Lieberman,

06:19.925 --> 06:22.202
do you remember anything
about last night?

06:30.039 --> 06:32.007
Derek was still wearing
his costume

06:32.041 --> 06:34.476
when was killed last night,
and he never made it to his car,

06:34.511 --> 06:37.896
which makes your party the last
place that he was seen alive.

06:37.931 --> 06:39.882
Well, he seemed fine
when he left, right?

06:39.916 --> 06:41.400
- I mean...
- Yeah.

06:41.434 --> 06:42.835
- Oh, thank you.
- Mm.

06:42.935 --> 06:44.786
Were there any problems
at the party,

06:44.837 --> 06:47.238
any jealous husbands
or boyfriends that showed up?

06:47.256 --> 06:48.976
No, it was--
it was just the girls.

06:49.776 --> 06:50.976
Who arranged the gig?

06:51.075 --> 06:53.877
I did. Jam-Jamie's always
had a thing for cops.

06:53.911 --> 06:55.879
It might interest you to know,

06:55.913 --> 06:58.915
I'm an assistant volunteer
Homicide Detective myself.

07:01.469 --> 07:03.211
How'd you set it up?

07:03.234 --> 07:05.025
The same way
you'd order a pizza.

07:05.122 --> 07:06.772
I called this place
that I found online,

07:06.791 --> 07:08.758
Mucho Men,
and gave my credit card.

07:08.893 --> 07:12.262
300 bucks an hour to send
my best friend off in style.

07:12.296 --> 07:14.567
Did he mention where
he was going after that?

07:14.788 --> 07:16.789
We were all wasted
by the time he showed up.

07:16.823 --> 07:19.392
I mean, he could've told me
his life story,

07:19.426 --> 07:20.477
and I wouldn't remember.

07:20.577 --> 07:22.327
Wait, a bachelorette party,
male stripper,

07:22.427 --> 07:27.164
loads of alcohol... one of you
had to be taking pictures.

07:29.915 --> 07:31.898
Well, here is the last one.

07:31.917 --> 07:34.168
I figured Jamie could
refer back to these...

07:34.202 --> 07:36.670
When she's old
and bored of her <i>marriage.</i>

07:42.110 --> 07:45.446
Oh. Tequila shots.

07:45.480 --> 07:47.382
- They're treating him like a piece of meat.
- It's okay.

07:47.439 --> 07:49.908
It's what he's paid for.
He had fun, too.

07:58.533 --> 08:00.118
Wait, wait, wait.
Stop on that one.

08:02.647 --> 08:03.215
Well, it's a good thing

08:03.315 --> 08:04.960
you took 30 pictures
of that one pose.

08:05.251 --> 08:06.819
Can you enhance
the background?

08:06.853 --> 08:08.487
Over there,
behind the group.

08:10.690 --> 08:12.641
- Who is that woman?
- Uh, that's Camille.

08:12.692 --> 08:15.144
She's a friend of Jamie's
from high school.

08:15.195 --> 08:16.531
It looks as though
she and Derek know each other.

08:16.631 --> 08:18.187
She never
mentioned anything.

08:18.287 --> 08:19.487
Can you enhance her face?

08:21.953 --> 08:25.222
She wasn't at the apartment
this morning. Where is she?

08:25.257 --> 08:26.891
She left...

08:26.925 --> 08:30.111
Right after Officer McNaughty.

08:34.331 --> 08:36.895
Turns out...
Camille Roberts has a record.

08:37.332 --> 08:38.636
Five years ago,
an ex-boyfriend

08:38.736 --> 08:39.947
filed a restraining order
against her

08:40.047 --> 08:41.549
after she threw all his stuff
out the window.

08:41.671 --> 08:44.006
Well, as a man who's dated
several rabbit boilers,

08:44.039 --> 08:45.333
I can safely say,
been there.

08:45.433 --> 08:46.308
Yeah, but a restraining order

08:46.409 --> 08:47.846
doesn't mean
that she's our killer.

08:47.946 --> 08:49.146
Yeah, except that
her ex-boyfriend

08:49.246 --> 08:50.846
happens to be our vic.

08:54.184 --> 08:56.918
Picked up Camille Roberts
at a café where she waitresses.

08:56.937 --> 08:58.520
She's in
interrogation room one.

08:58.738 --> 09:00.466
All right. What did we find
from Derek's apartment?

09:00.537 --> 09:02.087
Mostly just old movie posters

09:02.122 --> 09:03.918
and a bunch of Donald Trump
books about finance.

09:04.018 --> 09:05.986
Maybe Derek dreams about
being an entrepreneur,

09:06.004 --> 09:08.320
or maybe he's just a fan
of "Celebrity Apprentice."

09:08.368 --> 09:09.318
Anything else?

09:09.418 --> 09:10.652
There was a day planner
with nothing in it

09:10.687 --> 09:12.735
but a business card for a guy
named Jesse Mandalay.

09:12.935 --> 09:14.573
All right, run it.
I'll talk to Camille.

09:16.593 --> 09:19.993
This is like a bad dream.
I can't believe he's dead.

09:19.998 --> 09:22.512
Why did you leave the party
right after Derek did?

09:22.573 --> 09:24.541
I needed
to get outta there.

09:24.575 --> 09:26.209
And where did you go?

09:26.244 --> 09:29.112
Home. I just wanted
to be alone.

09:29.146 --> 09:32.048
You didn't see him
afterwards?

09:32.083 --> 09:34.451
I turned the corner,
and he was gone.

09:35.835 --> 09:38.256
Wait. You don't think I had
something to do with this?

09:38.356 --> 09:40.319
Camille, he had
a restraining order against you.

09:40.419 --> 09:43.388
That was years ago. It was
just a big misunderstanding.

09:43.422 --> 09:45.447
Look, Derek broke my heart,
but then I got over it.

09:46.142 --> 09:48.893
This... doesn't look like
the face of a person

09:48.928 --> 09:50.528
who got over it.

09:51.699 --> 09:53.666
When he walked into the party

09:53.701 --> 09:55.402
and started ripping
his clothes off, it upset me,

09:55.449 --> 09:56.430
but I didn't kill him.

09:56.530 --> 09:58.789
Okay. Why don't we just
go over the facts?

09:59.628 --> 10:01.696
You had a volatile relationship
with him,

10:01.730 --> 10:04.432
you left the party
the same time that Derek left,

10:04.466 --> 10:06.417
and then he turned up dead.

10:06.468 --> 10:09.337
So why don't you just tell me
what was really going on?

10:09.371 --> 10:12.006
Nothing. I just couldn't
believe he was stripping.

10:12.040 --> 10:13.671
And why was that
a shock to you?

10:13.771 --> 10:15.378
We met in acting class.

10:16.029 --> 10:18.631
He was the one everyone thought
was gonna hit it big.

10:18.665 --> 10:21.634
When I confronted him about
giving up on his dream,

10:21.668 --> 10:23.502
he said he was stripping

10:23.537 --> 10:25.471
because he was so desperate
for money.

10:25.505 --> 10:26.622
Did he tell you why?

10:27.568 --> 10:29.569
He had some other
recurring gig,

10:29.603 --> 10:32.872
but... he said he had to quit
'cause it was gonna kill him.

10:39.034 --> 10:40.783
My instinct says it's not her.

10:41.137 --> 10:42.424
Mine, too. But have C.S.U. check

10:42.524 --> 10:43.870
the clothes she was wearing
for gunshot residue.

10:44.039 --> 10:45.402
All right. Any luck
tracking down the gig

10:45.502 --> 10:46.624
that he was
telling Camille about?

10:46.724 --> 10:47.924
Derek has
a low-rent Theatrical Agent,

10:48.573 --> 10:50.359
says he hasn't booked anything
in over a year.

10:50.459 --> 10:52.794
He just e-mailed
Derek's acting reel.

10:52.845 --> 10:54.462
Here's a taste of his illustrious career.

10:54.513 --> 10:56.464
<i>Hey, there.</i>
<i>I'm just stopping a few couples</i>

10:56.515 --> 10:59.484
<i>to see if they've ever heard</i>
<i>of a product called Prolong.</i>

10:59.518 --> 11:02.754
<i>Are you kidding?</i>
<i>We just started using Prolong.</i>

11:02.772 --> 11:04.389
<i>Now...</i>

11:04.423 --> 11:07.692
<i>Things are really...</i>
<i>Looking up.</i>

11:09.015 --> 11:11.454
Prolong--now available
without a prescription.

11:11.554 --> 11:12.510
He also
did serious work.

11:13.149 --> 11:13.949
<i>Give me all your money</i>

11:13.956 --> 11:15.924
<i>and whatever parts you got</i>
<i>out there in that garage,</i>

11:15.958 --> 11:18.964
<i>and I'll consider not</i>
<i>putting one in your noggin'.</i>

11:19.705 --> 11:20.987
Billy Grimm is the leader

11:21.087 --> 11:22.821
of the Visi Goth
motorcycle gang.

11:22.855 --> 11:25.290
If you or anyone
has any information

11:25.324 --> 11:26.825
on this dangerous criminal,

11:26.859 --> 11:28.514
please contact
your local authority.

11:28.614 --> 11:31.330
Damn. I could see why the guy
had to strip to pay his bills.

11:31.430 --> 11:33.069
Well, I guess it's safe to say

11:33.169 --> 11:34.727
that the gig that he was
telling Camille about

11:34.827 --> 11:36.405
had nothing to do with his
acting pursuits,

11:36.406 --> 11:38.291
- so you guys head off to Mucho Men.
- Mucho Men?

11:38.374 --> 11:40.300
That's the place that booked him
for the bachelorette party.

11:40.400 --> 11:41.741
See if he had any regular stripping gigs...

11:41.841 --> 11:44.395
Or troubles there.
Beckett.

11:47.371 --> 11:49.405
He's not that handsome.

11:49.439 --> 11:51.908
You want my opinion?
300 bucks an hour--

11:51.942 --> 11:52.957
little steep.

11:53.057 --> 11:54.091
As the person in this room

11:54.165 --> 11:57.334
that's seen everything under
the sheet... Bargain.

11:59.235 --> 12:00.424
What else did you find?

12:01.053 --> 12:03.788
Take a look.

12:05.198 --> 12:06.933
A hair?

12:06.944 --> 12:08.945
Your vic has hair that's been
recently dyed gray.

12:08.980 --> 12:10.447
Looks like temporary hair dye

12:10.481 --> 12:12.449
that hasn't completely
washed out yet.

12:12.483 --> 12:14.651
Well, most men color
their hair to cover the gray.

12:14.685 --> 12:16.720
Well, some women want
Officer McNaughty,

12:16.754 --> 12:18.337
and some want an older guy
who knows mutual funds.

12:18.437 --> 12:19.973
You know, daddy issues.

12:20.373 --> 12:22.968
It's more likely he was
coloring it for an audition.

12:23.359 --> 12:26.552
Speaking of hair, this is
the more important hair

12:26.645 --> 12:28.258
that I found
on your vic's clothing.

12:28.304 --> 12:30.255
That <i>could</i>
belong to our killer.

12:30.306 --> 12:31.773
A long, blonde hair.

12:31.807 --> 12:33.308
Well, this could've come

12:33.342 --> 12:35.310
from one of the women
at the bachelorette party.

12:35.344 --> 12:37.679
That's what I thought
until I had it tested.

12:37.713 --> 12:39.681
Came back positive
for testosterone

12:39.715 --> 12:41.216
and anabolic steroids.

12:41.250 --> 12:44.953
Your blondie is a man.

12:46.687 --> 12:50.389
