<i>and I'll consider not puttin'</i>
<i>one in your noggin'.</i>

26:15.715 --> 26:17.365
Billy Grimm is the--

26:19.168 --> 26:22.204
That's the same guy
as the mug shot.

26:23.756 --> 26:25.474
Billy Grimm--

26:25.508 --> 26:30.345
leader of the Visi Goths
motorcycle gang.

26:30.379 --> 26:32.130
Billy Grimm's rap sheet.

26:33.015 --> 26:35.717
Extortion, assault with
a deadly weapon, armed robbery.

26:35.735 --> 26:37.219
When Derek's episode

26:37.253 --> 26:39.071
of "America's Most Dangerous
Criminals" aired,

26:39.105 --> 26:40.460
Grimm had an attempt murder
warrant out.

26:40.560 --> 26:42.180
Apparently some guy owed him
money, so he chained him

26:42.280 --> 26:45.332
to the back of his bike
and dragged him down the L.I.E.

26:45.333 --> 26:46.343
Why isn't this psycho Grimm
in jail?

26:46.475 --> 26:48.213
He was, as a matter of fact,
he was caught

26:48.460 --> 26:50.411
because of Derek's reenactment
on the show.

26:50.445 --> 26:53.047
But the guy he chained to his
bike had a change of heart,

26:53.081 --> 26:56.117
refused to testify, so Grimm
was recently released from jail.

26:56.151 --> 26:57.222
Well, if this guy
was such a whack job,

26:57.322 --> 26:59.891
what was Derek doing talking to
one of the members of his gang?

27:00.158 --> 27:02.109
I think I can answer that.
When Grimm was arrested,

27:02.160 --> 27:04.111
a reporter
asked him how he felt

27:04.162 --> 27:06.979
about being brought to justice
by a TV show.

27:07.079 --> 27:09.364
He swore vengeance against
those who put him jail,

27:09.415 --> 27:11.649
especially--and Grimm says,

27:11.667 --> 27:14.752
"that actor that made me look
like a clown."

27:14.787 --> 27:15.908
I can tell you this
about Visi Goths

27:16.008 --> 27:17.544
from my gang task force days--

27:17.644 --> 27:19.111
they're serious
about their colors.

27:19.145 --> 27:21.113
These patches
they wear on their vests?

27:21.147 --> 27:21.913
They're not varsity letters.

27:22.013 --> 27:24.014
They gotta spill blood
to get 'em.

27:24.048 --> 27:25.565
And some guy wearing 'em
on national TV?

27:25.665 --> 27:26.865
So she was setting him up...

27:29.073 --> 27:30.974
For murder.

27:34.202 --> 27:36.888
♪

27:43.275 --> 27:44.885
Relax, Castle.
It's on a chain.

27:47.355 --> 27:48.688
NYPD.

27:48.722 --> 27:51.024
This your old lady?

27:54.061 --> 27:56.529
♪

27:56.563 --> 27:58.498
This is
a private establishment.

27:58.532 --> 28:00.500
Well, then we'll try to
keep this private.

28:00.534 --> 28:02.836
Billy Grimm.

28:02.870 --> 28:04.170
Bobby!

28:04.205 --> 28:06.572
Yo!

28:06.591 --> 28:08.158
I need to ask you
a few questions

28:08.258 --> 28:10.250
about your association
with Derek Brookner.

28:11.969 --> 28:13.035
Never heard of the guy.

28:13.135 --> 28:15.871
I make one phone call, and auto
theft detail is down here

28:15.905 --> 28:17.472
checking VIN numbers.

28:17.506 --> 28:21.710
They find so much as a stolen
taillight, you're violated.

28:21.744 --> 28:23.545
You remember him now?

28:23.579 --> 28:25.380
♪

28:26.716 --> 28:30.218
You know, I do.

28:30.236 --> 28:32.187
He seemed like a good kid.

28:32.221 --> 28:34.868
He's dead,
and I'm willing to bet

28:34.968 --> 28:36.418
that you had something
to do with it.

28:36.518 --> 28:37.436
Derek wore the colors,

28:37.537 --> 28:38.684
and you got popped
'cause of the show.

28:38.784 --> 28:41.430
That's why you put
a contract out on him.

28:41.530 --> 28:44.048
Well, I might have been
a little pissed off.

28:44.099 --> 28:46.050
But the kid came with respect.

28:46.101 --> 28:48.052
He brought a donation.

28:48.103 --> 28:50.071
A donation? What are you,
The Salvation Army?

28:50.105 --> 28:52.640
Well, I was surprised, too,
but I guess Derek felt

28:52.674 --> 28:54.722
25 g's might help
bring down my overhead.

28:54.890 --> 28:57.024
Do you really
expect me to believe

28:57.042 --> 28:59.026
that a struggling actor
had enough money

28:59.044 --> 29:01.095
to give you 25 grand
outta nowhere?

29:01.130 --> 29:02.630
That's what happened.

29:02.664 --> 29:04.005
Where did he get
the money?

29:04.105 --> 29:06.474
I didn't ask to see
his friggin' tax return.

29:06.508 --> 29:08.575
Ain't my business
how he got the money.

29:08.675 --> 29:11.210
He brought the cash,
and that was good enough.

29:11.245 --> 29:13.479
Aren't you forgetting
the part about the extortion,

29:13.513 --> 29:15.781
the part where you asked your
girlfriend to deliver a message

29:15.816 --> 29:18.434
that Derek had to pay you
25 grand?

29:18.485 --> 29:19.789
You gave him a week to do it.

29:19.889 --> 29:21.269
He couldn't scrape together
the money,

29:21.369 --> 29:23.938
and so you killed him.

29:30.957 --> 29:32.824
Babe, what is this?

29:32.858 --> 29:34.659
I can explain.

29:34.694 --> 29:36.962
What the hell were you doing
talking to that bitch?

29:36.996 --> 29:38.118
Listen,
when you got outta jail,

29:38.218 --> 29:40.389
I got nervous you were
gonna do something stupid,

29:40.489 --> 29:42.963
so I went to talk to the kid,
told him if he didn't want

29:43.063 --> 29:46.128
any trouble, he'd bring you
a preemptive donation.

29:46.165 --> 29:48.166
So you warned him?
That's why he showed up here?

29:48.200 --> 29:51.002
I couldn't stand the thought
of losing you again.

29:51.036 --> 29:54.722
The only way you're going back
to jail is over my dead body.

29:56.512 --> 29:59.147
Pookiebear...

29:59.182 --> 30:03.084
That is the most romantic thing
I've ever heard, baby.

30:03.102 --> 30:04.586
Come here.

30:04.604 --> 30:06.921
Mm.

30:06.940 --> 30:08.640
♪

30:08.691 --> 30:10.642
mm.

30:10.693 --> 30:12.562
♪

30:12.657 --> 30:14.925
Hey. Billy's alibi
checked out.

30:14.959 --> 30:17.094
Bartender confirmed that he was
shooting pool till close.

30:17.128 --> 30:19.596
Yeah, and we talked to
our C.I., and there's no word

30:19.631 --> 30:22.165
of our victim hitting up
any of the usual loan sharks.

30:22.183 --> 30:23.986
You know what I want to know
is how a stripper comes up

30:24.086 --> 30:25.499
with that kind of cash
in such a hurry?

30:25.599 --> 30:27.055
Cash-n-Gold.

30:27.443 --> 30:29.243
Castle, you watch
way too many infomercials.

30:29.278 --> 30:31.646
We also checked his account
at JLP Bank Corp.

30:31.680 --> 30:33.082
He never carried
an account balance

30:33.096 --> 30:34.080
of more than
a couple thousand dollars.

30:34.180 --> 30:37.532
Wait a minute. If Derek had
an account with JLP Bank Corp.,

30:37.566 --> 30:41.069
why was there a deposit slip
from Rampart Federal in his car?

30:43.350 --> 30:45.332
Let's run down withdrawals
for 25 grand

30:45.432 --> 30:46.899
from Rampart Federal branches

30:46.933 --> 30:48.719
for the day
that Derek paid Billy.

30:48.819 --> 30:51.470
I don't know
how you missed that.

30:53.338 --> 30:54.217
Yo.

30:54.749 --> 30:58.001
Rampart Federal on 93rd
posted a transaction that size,

30:58.052 --> 31:01.354
made by a Jesse Mandalay
at 11:53 A.M. that day.

31:01.389 --> 31:02.439
Derek had a card

31:02.539 --> 31:04.506
for Jesse Mandalay
tucked inside one of his books.

31:04.541 --> 31:05.807
I called the number.
It was disconnected.

31:05.907 --> 31:06.942
It's possible that Mandalay

31:07.043 --> 31:08.279
was the one
that loaned Derek the money.

31:08.379 --> 31:10.631
Maybe Derek thought he was on
a flexible payment plan,

31:10.731 --> 31:12.687
needed more time,
and Mandalay killed him for it.

31:12.787 --> 31:14.489
Well, the bank is sending over
the surveillance footage

31:14.589 --> 31:16.957
of Mandalay right now.

31:21.932 --> 31:25.931
Here we go. There's Mandalay
taking the cash.

31:26.266 --> 31:27.051
Yeah,
by the looks of that suit,

31:27.151 --> 31:29.052
the loan business
must be pretty lucrative.

31:29.330 --> 31:30.433
Okay, let's see
this guy's face.

31:31.629 --> 31:32.401
Wait, wait, wait.

31:32.415 --> 31:35.383
That's not Jesse Mandalay.
That's Derek with gray hair.

31:36.740 --> 31:39.575
Jesse Mandalay is Derek.

31:45.755 --> 31:47.972
The branch manager said
that Derek withdrew money

31:49.977 --> 31:50.435
from an account
called Sunfire Limited.

31:50.535 --> 31:52.379
And his alter ego
Jesse Mandalay?

31:52.479 --> 31:54.967
Was the signatory,
but the rest is a mystery.

31:55.226 --> 31:57.760
Sunfire is linked
to an offshore account,

31:57.795 --> 32:00.163
and the only person that they
can trace it to is Mandalay.

32:00.197 --> 32:02.428
A money trail that leads back
to a man who doesn't exist.

32:02.528 --> 32:04.496
Derek was dyeing
his hair gray,

32:04.530 --> 32:07.499
wearing fancy suits
to look more distinguished,

32:07.533 --> 32:10.502
and he was reading books
on finance and investment

32:10.536 --> 32:15.838
so that he could play the role
of Jesse Mandalay for someone.

32:16.605 --> 32:19.574
But why hire a struggling actor
to play a businessman?

32:19.608 --> 32:22.827
I did some research on
Chinese companies that would,

32:22.878 --> 32:24.846
uh, sometimes hire
a-a white man

32:24.880 --> 32:27.848
to pose as an executive at, uh,
ribbon cutting ceremonies,

32:28.002 --> 32:29.136
uh, shareholder meetings,

32:29.158 --> 32:30.992
just to instill confidence
in investors.

32:31.027 --> 32:34.068
Likewise, a college student
seeking Venture Capital

32:34.168 --> 32:36.553
will sometimes hire
an older-looking shill,

32:36.587 --> 32:38.454
you know, someone who looks
more, uh, distinguished

32:38.554 --> 32:39.683
to help them secure money.

32:39.783 --> 32:42.578
So if Derek was hired to be
the face of the company,

32:42.678 --> 32:43.912
then whoever hired him

32:43.923 --> 32:45.891
was the person
behind the bank account.

32:45.925 --> 32:48.193
Let's see if we can
track down any checks

32:48.228 --> 32:50.562
that were deposited
into Sunfire Limited recently.

32:50.596 --> 32:53.532
If we can trace the money,
maybe we can figure out

32:53.566 --> 32:56.535
if Jesse Mandalay
was a role to die for.

32:56.569 --> 33:00.939
Yeah. That's Mandalay.
100%. Why?

33:00.974 --> 33:03.509
Miss Lombardo, we need to know
about the $10,000 check

33:03.543 --> 33:05.179
that you wrote him
a couple of days ago.

33:05.279 --> 33:06.503
Sure.
Best money I ever spent.

33:06.603 --> 33:07.803
What was the money for?

33:08.416 --> 33:09.866
An exciting
investment opportunity.

33:09.917 --> 33:11.985
My girlfriend Sammi heard from
her boyfriend Ronni

33:12.019 --> 33:13.987
who heard
from his cousin Pauly

33:14.021 --> 33:15.922
about Mr. Mandalay's
presentation.

33:15.957 --> 33:17.924
And what was the sales pitch?

33:17.959 --> 33:19.926
The beautiful Braverman Lofts

33:19.961 --> 33:21.962
in idyllic riverfront Hoboken.

33:21.996 --> 33:23.427
And Mandalay
was there himself?

33:24.208 --> 33:25.322
He gave us the awesome news

33:25.422 --> 33:27.258
that if we put down
the $10,000 that day,

33:27.358 --> 33:30.494
we could purchase a loft
for $400,000.

33:31.635 --> 33:32.861
A riverfront loft?

33:32.961 --> 33:34.586
I know. Amazing, right?

33:34.897 --> 33:38.366
Uh, um... amazing is--
is one word for it, yes.

33:38.400 --> 33:40.801
Yeah, you have to be, like,
a freakin' bonehead

33:40.819 --> 33:42.318
to pass up
on a deal like that.

33:42.418 --> 33:44.489
Did anyone else
at the presentation hand over

33:44.589 --> 33:45.505
a check to Mandalay that day?

33:45.605 --> 33:48.754
Uh, everyone.
My dad was pretty butt sore

33:48.854 --> 33:50.437
that I took the money
out of my college fund,

33:50.537 --> 33:52.319
but when I explained
that it would fold

33:52.419 --> 33:53.886
into the purchase price,

33:53.921 --> 33:56.822
he recognized that business
smarts runs in our family.

33:56.857 --> 33:58.291
Let me guess.

33:58.325 --> 34:00.960
The, uh, the contract
is in the mail, right?

34:06.900 --> 34:08.868
Yeah, this is it.
The Braverman Lofts.

34:08.902 --> 34:14.239
And that must be
the showroom.

34:14.274 --> 34:17.376
Oh.

34:17.411 --> 34:21.313
$400,000 for one of these?
I'll take 2.

34:21.331 --> 34:22.982
Castle, let's go.

34:23.000 --> 34:24.650
Excuse me.

34:24.668 --> 34:26.452
Can I help you?

34:26.485 --> 34:28.454
NYPD. Who's in charge here?

34:28.487 --> 34:31.958
I am. I'm the developer--
Bert Kramer.

34:31.992 --> 34:34.927
We're here about Jesse Mandalay.
Do you know him?

34:34.962 --> 34:37.929
Unfortunately, and if I ever
see that guy again, I'm gonna

34:37.965 --> 34:39.991
bust him in the jaw for all
the crap he put me through.

34:40.091 --> 34:40.922
Let me guess.

34:40.967 --> 34:42.935
He took advantage of you.
Damn right.

34:42.969 --> 34:44.904
He tried to sell my friggin'
property like it was his.

34:44.938 --> 34:47.556
Showed up here claiming to be
a real estate Agent,

34:47.608 --> 34:50.476
and he had this rap about
all these properties he's sold.

34:50.510 --> 34:51.831
And you gave him access
to the building?

34:51.931 --> 34:53.992
Well, he wanted to bring
a caravan of clients through,

34:54.092 --> 34:56.076
and he insisted
it be on a Sunday,

34:56.094 --> 34:58.078
so I gave him
the lockbox codes.

34:58.096 --> 34:59.289
How did you find out
he wasn't legit?

34:59.389 --> 35:00.589
Ever since that day,

35:00.605 --> 35:03.441
I got people showing up saying
they got the Mandalay deal

35:03.475 --> 35:05.109
and threatening to sue.

35:05.143 --> 35:07.111
Well,
we have reason to believe

35:07.145 --> 35:09.380
that Mandalay was working
with a partner.

35:09.414 --> 35:11.382
Did anyone else contact you?

35:11.416 --> 35:13.150
Uh, no.

35:13.185 --> 35:16.153
And when the tents folded up,
it was radio silence.

35:16.188 --> 35:18.222
But I did call
some of the other developers,

35:18.256 --> 35:20.207
and sure enough,
this Mandalay guy,

35:20.258 --> 35:22.209
he brought caravans
to their properties.

35:22.260 --> 35:25.830
Now they're dealing
with the same mess.

35:25.864 --> 35:28.165
Do you have any brochures?

35:28.200 --> 35:30.601
I'm looking for a place.
Mine blew up.

35:30.635 --> 35:32.470
10 grand a pop

35:32.504 --> 35:33.971
all over Jersey.

35:34.005 --> 35:35.473
That adds up quick.

35:35.507 --> 35:37.475
I don't understand
why Derek was still working

35:37.509 --> 35:39.477
as a stripper
the night that he was killed

35:39.511 --> 35:40.977
if he was involved in a scam

35:41.077 --> 35:42.269
that was raking in
that much money.

35:42.369 --> 35:43.913
Because he wasn't the one
raking in all the dough.

35:43.931 --> 35:45.848
He was just the actor,
hired for his looks

35:45.883 --> 35:48.334
and his personality
to charm the investors.

35:48.369 --> 35:50.937
So all along, Derek sees his partner
taking the money to the bank...

35:50.938 --> 35:52.924
And when he gets in trouble
with the bikers

35:53.024 --> 35:54.550
and suddenly he needs cash...

35:54.650 --> 35:56.911
He raids the bank account for
the 25 grand that he needs,

35:57.011 --> 35:58.528
and his partner
figures it out.

35:58.628 --> 35:59.728
Which leads
to a heated confrontation

36:00.086 --> 36:02.053
where he admits
to borrowing the money,

36:02.088 --> 36:04.467
but... but he says
he's pulling out of the scam.

36:08.844 --> 36:10.178
Beckett.

36:12.098 --> 36:13.932
Got it. Thanks.

36:15.301 --> 36:17.268
Ryan and Esposito did
a little bit of digging,

36:17.303 --> 36:19.604
and they found the real owner
of the Sunfire account

36:19.638 --> 36:21.225
that Derek used
to withdraw the money.

36:21.312 --> 36:22.946
The Articles of Incorporation

36:22.980 --> 36:25.448
were signed by our very own
orchid-loving widow--

36:25.483 --> 36:27.576
Rebecca Dalton.

36:27.676 --> 36:28.876
Shut the front door.

36:34.263 --> 36:36.110
Beckett,
you sure about this?

36:36.269 --> 36:37.885
Sir, it's all right here
in black and white.

36:37.997 --> 36:39.692
We tracked the money
from the real estate scam

36:39.792 --> 36:42.344
to this offshore account
in the Cayman Islands.

36:42.373 --> 36:44.675
So Derek decides he's done
playing the Mandalay role,

36:44.709 --> 36:47.644
and because he knows too much,
the only option is to kill him.

36:47.679 --> 36:49.379
Hey. You were right.

36:49.397 --> 36:51.765
I was able to confirm
Rebecca Dalton's whereabouts.

36:51.816 --> 36:54.267
Get a warrant to search
for the murder weapon.

36:55.512 --> 36:58.464
As someone who's written just
about every ending in the book,

36:58.515 --> 37:01.484
can I just say...
Amazing?

37:01.518 --> 37:05.722
You can say that
<i>after</i> we get the confession.

37:05.756 --> 37:08.725
Ms. Dalton, we did a thorough
search of your finances.

37:08.759 --> 37:11.432
You've lost quite a lot of money
since your husband passed away.

37:11.532 --> 37:13.557
My client doesn't need
to defend her spending habits.

37:13.657 --> 37:16.063
She does if it's relevant
to my case.

37:16.163 --> 37:18.264
What does my money have to do
with Derek's death?

37:18.543 --> 37:19.911
Everything, actually.

37:19.968 --> 37:22.736
Let's see, there is a clothing
line that never took off,

37:22.771 --> 37:25.372
a, uh,
failed jewelry business.

37:25.440 --> 37:26.537
I mean, should I go on?

37:26.637 --> 37:28.433
That doesn't make me
a murderer.

37:28.576 --> 37:29.673
Well, it was
only a matter of time

37:29.773 --> 37:31.117
until all the money was gone.

37:31.217 --> 37:33.062
Derek was handsome,
he was charming.

37:33.162 --> 37:34.428
You knew
he was a decent actor.

37:35.398 --> 37:37.365
It made him the perfect guy
to present investors

37:37.400 --> 37:39.051
with an opportunity
they couldn't refuse.

37:39.151 --> 37:40.915
This is wildly speculative,

37:41.015 --> 37:42.835
and your allegations
are baseless.

37:42.935 --> 37:45.837
Derek took 25 grand
from an account

37:45.871 --> 37:48.072
that initially led us
in circles--

37:48.090 --> 37:49.674
the Sunfire account.

37:51.510 --> 37:54.245
Well, this isn't possible.
I didn't even sign this.

37:54.263 --> 37:56.381
Rebecca, I'm advising you,
don't say another word.

37:56.415 --> 37:58.550
Wait a minute.
September 29th?

37:58.584 --> 38:01.586
I wasn't even
in the country.

38:01.620 --> 38:03.221
We know.

38:03.255 --> 38:05.423
The date it was signed?

38:05.457 --> 38:07.825
Smack-dab in the middle
of Paris Fashion Week.

38:08.198 --> 38:10.332
I knew that any former model

38:10.367 --> 38:11.544
worth her salt
would've been there,

38:11.644 --> 38:13.463
and of course,
after checking flight records,

38:13.563 --> 38:15.164
you were in Paris.

38:15.198 --> 38:17.166
Yes, and while you were
drinking champagne,

38:17.200 --> 38:20.826
your lawyer was using
his access to your information

38:20.926 --> 38:22.993
to create a scam
in your name.

38:23.028 --> 38:25.329
Oh, he was also
stealing from you,

38:25.363 --> 38:27.331
funneling the money
into his offshore account.

38:27.365 --> 38:29.133
That's why
your businesses failed.

38:29.167 --> 38:32.369
He offered Derek a job
behind your back

38:32.404 --> 38:33.904
to play Jesse Mandalay.

38:33.939 --> 38:35.406
The money was decent,

38:35.440 --> 38:37.618
but when the bikers came after
Derek, he needed more.

38:37.842 --> 38:40.074
Oh, my God.
Michael, what did you do?

38:40.130 --> 38:42.932
When you found out that Derek
made an unauthorized withdrawal,

38:42.967 --> 38:44.434
you confronted him,

38:44.468 --> 38:46.319
but he knew that
you couldn't go to the cops,

38:46.598 --> 38:49.066
so he told you
that he wanted out.

38:49.100 --> 38:51.068
You couldn't afford him
exposing your fraud,

38:51.102 --> 38:53.170
so you followed him
from his apartment,

38:53.204 --> 38:55.372
and then killed him
that night.

39:00.747 --> 39:03.048
I'm not saying
another word.

39:03.082 --> 39:05.350
Do you want a lawyer...

39:05.385 --> 39:09.087
Or do you want to hire an actor
to play one for you?

39:10.890 --> 39:13.158
So what happened with
your struggling actor case?

39:13.176 --> 39:15.160
Well, they found
the murder weapon

39:15.178 --> 39:15.929
at the lawyer's office.

39:16.032 --> 39:18.274
He confessed in an effort
to cut a deal.

39:18.374 --> 39:20.055
Oh, God. It's so sad.

39:20.155 --> 39:21.775
The poor kid was just
trying to catch a break,

39:21.875 --> 39:24.377
and he kept stepping
in the dog poo.

39:24.411 --> 39:27.046
You should stitch that on to a pillow.

39:27.080 --> 39:29.539
Oh! Hey, sweetie.

39:29.639 --> 39:31.796
Do we have a Sandra Dee
in our midst?

39:31.891 --> 39:34.259
I didn't get the part.

39:34.310 --> 39:35.877
Oh.

39:35.895 --> 39:39.347
Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh,

39:39.382 --> 39:40.899
oh, honey.

39:44.770 --> 39:48.356
This is... the best thing
that has ever happened to you.

39:48.391 --> 39:51.392
Wh-- rejection is the bedrock
of a great acting career.

39:51.410 --> 39:55.197
Until an actor has suffered,
he hasn't really lived.

39:55.231 --> 39:56.731
Thanks, gram.

39:56.766 --> 39:58.233
You're welcome.

39:58.267 --> 40:00.702
And besides,
auditions are like men.

40:00.736 --> 40:02.704
There's another one
right around the corner.

40:02.738 --> 40:04.289
Yeah.

40:06.209 --> 40:07.414
Where are you going?

40:07.838 --> 40:10.540
Oh, we need ice cream
to ease the pain, stat.

40:10.558 --> 40:12.509
I'm going to the corner store.

40:12.543 --> 40:14.010
I am sorry, sweetie.

40:14.044 --> 40:15.897
Can I admit something?

40:15.997 --> 40:17.198
Always.

40:17.756 --> 40:18.623
Going up against Kelly

40:18.724 --> 40:21.125
made me realize, I didn't
really want the part.

40:21.160 --> 40:22.361
I could see how hungry she was,

40:22.363 --> 40:23.664
and I didn't want
to disappoint gram,

40:23.685 --> 40:25.220
but I don't love it
the way she does.

40:25.260 --> 40:28.696
Well, maybe it's not "in your
bones," as gram would say.

40:31.019 --> 40:33.354
I am proud of you for trying.

40:33.388 --> 40:35.606
Thanks, dad.
And there's a silver lining.

40:35.657 --> 40:36.624
After the announcement,

40:36.631 --> 40:38.041
the drama teacher offered me
stage manager.

40:38.133 --> 40:39.361
It's way more my style,

40:39.511 --> 40:41.075
and I get to keep
all my after-school clubs.

40:42.013 --> 40:43.480
My little overachiever.

40:44.505 --> 40:46.506
Well, congratulations
on not getting the part.

40:46.540 --> 40:49.292
♪ yes we will, yes we will ♪

40:49.343 --> 40:50.793
mmm. What smells good?

40:50.844 --> 40:53.296
Come help me. Wash up...

